para_trans: On the occasion of Gopalakala (Dahihandi) and Anant Chaturdashi
Regarding the announcement of a local holiday...
Government Circular No: Sarvasu-1125 / P.No.199 / Japuk (29)
Mantralaya, Madam Cama Marg, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk,
Government Circular, General Administration Department No.1196 / Q. 5/96/29, dated 18th September, 1996
Under the "Anant Chaturdashi" scheme, government / semi-government offices in Mumbai city and Mumbai Suburban district are observed every year.

On this day and since 2007, a local holiday is declared for Mumbai city and Mumbai suburban districts on the occasion of Gopalaka (Dahi Handi). Accordingly, in the year 2026, Mumbai and Mumbai will be as follows:
It has declared a local holiday for all government / semi-government offices in the suburban district.
These orders shall be applicable to the State Government / Subordinate Government offices in the city of Mumbai and the Mumbai Suburban District.
The above local holiday in Government Decision No. P & S. No. P-13 / II / B, dated November 5, 1958.
Announcement is being made as per the provision.
4. The circular will be made available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
